@startuml Business-Driven-Development-Current-Concise
title Current Business-Driven Development Workflow - Concise

!log Current 'STYLE' dvar: STYLE
!log About to include: styles/github-STYLE.puml
!include styles/github-STYLE.puml

participant "User" as User
participant "Claude Code" as Claude
participant "AI Agent" as Agent

== Business-Driven Development (Recommended) ==

alt Business Input Options
    User -> User: Create business_inputs/project.md
else Interactive Session
    User -> Claude: Interactive BRD generation
else Partial BRD
    User -> User: Partially fill BRDs/project.md
end

User -> Claude: make brd_gen_claude
Claude -> Agent: Generate BRD from business input
Agent -> User: **Comprehensive BRD**

User -> Claude: make prd_gen_claude
Claude -> Agent: Transform BRD to product features
Agent -> User: **PRD** with feature list

User -> Claude: make frp_gen_claude
Claude -> Agent: Create feature-specific technical spec
Agent -> User: **FRP** with business context

User -> Claude: make frp_exe_claude
Claude -> Agent: Implement with full context
Agent -> User: **Feature** with business traceability

== Direct Feature Development (Legacy) ==

User -> User: Create features/feature.md
User -> Claude: make frp_gen_legacy_claude
Claude -> Agent: Generate FRP from feature
Agent -> User: Technical spec (limited context)

User -> Claude: make frp_exe_legacy_claude
Claude -> Agent: Quick implementation
Agent -> User: Feature prototype

@enduml